quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  17,59,"And nothing prevented Us from sending<i class=""s"">(miraculous) </i>signs except that the ancients disbelieved in them. So We gave Thamûd{1}the she-camel as an eye-opener, but they mistreated it. For We never send signs except to frighten<i class=""s"">(people of destruction) </i>.",footnotes:1:The pagan tribe of Prophet Salih.
  17,60,"And recall when We said to you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>that your Lord{1}has encompassed mankind. And We did not make the vision We showed you except as a means of trial for mankind, and<i class=""s"">(recall) </i>the tree which is cursed in the Recital{2}. And We frighten them, but that increases them in nothing but supreme transgression.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 1st person to 3rd person.|2:The Arabic word used is Qur’anwhich literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  17,61,"And recall when We said to the angels, “Prostrate to Adam,” so they prostrated—but not Iblis{1}. He said, “Shall I prostrate down to someone You created of clay?”",footnotes:1:Iblis is another name of Satan or Shaytan.
  17,62,"He said, “Do You see this one whom You have honored more than me? If You reprieve me until the Day of Resurrection, I will most surely bridle his offspring, except for a few.”"
  17,63,"He said, “Go! Whoever of them follows you—then indeed, Hell is your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>repayment, an ample repayment."
  17,64,"And entice whomever of them youcan with your voice, and rally against them your cavalry and your infantry, and share with them in wealth and children, and promise them.” But Satan promises them nothing but a deception."
  17,65,"“You surely have no authority over My servants.” And sufficient is your Lord as a trustee."
  17,66,"Your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>Lord is the One Who propels for you the ships at sea, that you may seek of His grace; indeed, to you He has always been Merciful."
